{"id": 225003862, "title": "'She\u2019s mastered the art of complicity': Ex-Melania aide pans her hush money trial silence", "text": "With Donald Trump's hush money trial wrapping up in a Manhattan courtroom, and with the jury expected to be sent off for deliberations on Wednesday, a former aide to ex-first lady Melania Trump said it is no surprise she is a no-show with her husband facing prison time. In a blunt column for the Daily Beast, Stephanie Winston Wolkoff cut right to the chase and accused her former boss of maintaining a \"fa\u00e7ade of calm\" in the storm because it keeps her from having to face scrutiny. More to the point, she added, she noted Melania Trump \"isn\u2019t an enigma or a mystery. She is simply self-possessed, stoically guarded, and emotionally armored.\" ALSO READ: What Trump's weird WWE Hall of Fame speech tells us about his presidential debate strategy According to Winston Wolkoff, Melania Trump is a mirror image of her husband in that she, \"... lives by the same principles. She\u2019s a ruthless survivor and opportunist\u2014willing to do whatever it takes to resort to any means necessary for self-preservation. She\u2019s mastered the art of complicity.\" \"Melania\u2019s existence is predicated on always minimizing the impact of Donald\u2019s often despicable behavior. Her defense mechanism is her ability to lock the door and throw away the key to most anything that brings her emotional discomfort. The secret to her happiness is to be authentically and unapologetically skin-deep,\" she elaborated before adding, \"Melania never had any great expectations of Donald as a faithful husband or doting father.\" Noting that Melania confided to her, \"Just let him do what he\u2019s going to do. Why get in a fight about something that won\u2019t change?\" she added, \"little did I realize how merciless and unscrupulous she was in her relentless pursuit of power. Melania, like Donald, had told me many times that she wanted to win and that meant at all costs.\" You can read more here.", "summary": "<img src=\"https://www.rawstory.com/media-library/image.jpg?id=52350373&width=1200&height=800&coordinates=0%2C0%2C144%2C0\"/><br/><br/><p>With Donald Trump's hush money trial wrapping up in a Manhattan courtroom, and with the jury expected to be sent off for deliberations on Wednesday, a former aide to <a href=\"https://www.thedailybeast.com/whats-melania-thinking-during-trumps-criminal-hush-money-trial?ref=home\" target=\"_blank\">ex-first lady Melania Trump</a> said it is no surprise she is a no-show with <a href=\"https://www.rawstory.com/trump-stormy-daniels-2668402686/\" target=\"_blank\">her husband facing prison time.</a></p><p>In a blunt column for the Daily Beast, Stephanie Winston Wolkoff cut right to the chase and accused her former boss of maintaining a \"fa\u00e7ade of calm\" in the storm because it keeps her <a href=\"https://www.rawstory.com/melania-chief-of-staff-hush-money-humiliated/\" target=\"_blank\">from having to face scrutiny</a>.</p><p>More to the point, she added, she noted Melania Trump \"isn\u2019t an enigma", "url": "https://www.rawstory.com/melania-stormy-daniels/", "image": "https://www.rawstory.com/media-library/image.jpg?id=52350373&width=1200&height=600&coordinates=0%2C0%2C0%2C37", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:05:43", "author": "Tom Boggioni", "authors": ["Tom Boggioni"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.121}